CONTENT_29:
A large percentage of TTM&#146;s business is conducted with customers who are in the telecommunications industry and, after the consummation of the Merger, a large percentage of our business after giving
effect to the Merger is expected to continue to be conducted with such customers. This industry is characterized by intense competition, relatively short product life cycles, and significant fluctuations in product demand. This industry is heavily
dependent on the end markets it serves and therefore can be affected by the demand patterns of those markets. If the volatility in this industry continues, it would have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition, and results of
operations.
